Beast made 117 appearances in the green and gold jersey since his debut in 2008. JOHANNESBURG - Rugby World Cup-winning Springbok legend Tendai ‘Beast’ Mtawarira announced his retirement from international rugby on Wednesday. Beast made 117 appearances in the green and gold jersey since his debut in 2008. The 34-year-old - who was part of the team that won the Rugby World Cup over the weekend - is also the most capped prop for SA.